<paragraph id="8628475BFF878534FF13FF3CFB2AFEF0" blockId="32.[136,1452,158,365]" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF878534FF13FF3CFEE9FF40" bold="true" box="[189,294,194,220]" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">Notes:—</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF878534FE88FF3CFDE9FF40" authorityName="Kolanowska &amp; Szlachetko" authorityYear="2014" box="[294,550,194,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="32" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ortizianus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF878534FE88FF3CFDE9FF40" box="[294,550,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">Myoxanthus ortizianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="41973CD8FF878534FD17FF3DFCFBFF40" authorityName="Luer" authorityYear="1983" box="[697,820,195,220]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Myoxanthus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="32" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="priapus">
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF878534FD17FF3DFCFBFF40" box="[697,820,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">M. priapus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; they share the purple-yellow flowers covered abaxially with short trichomes, lateral sepals forming a suborbicular synsepal, petals yellowish purple-stripped, obovate to oblong basally, then contracted, and lip with a thick, erect basal callus. However, the former is distinguished by its narrower petal apex forming a slender tail 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF878534FDC7FED1FD4FFED4" box="[617,640,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">vs</emphasis>
. apex narrow not forming a slender tail, and a scarcely trilobed lip with rounded lateral lobes below the middle 
<emphasis id="B4E39B49FF878534FDEDFEADFD95FEF0" box="[579,602,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="243">vs</emphasis>
. lip oblong with small acute lateral lobes near the middle.
</paragraph>
